cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses the design and optimization of medium access control protocols for cognitive radio networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of information theory (cs.IT) to analyze the performance of the proposed protocols. Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of spectrum sharing (cs.CR) and the integration of cooperative sensing (cs.SY) in the protocol design. Finally, the paper discusses the use of full-duplex communication (cs.MM) in cognitive radio networks.
